# Language Specification

## Code Comments and Documentation Language
**English** - All code comments, documentation, commit messages, and inline documentation must be written in English.

## Rationale
- Maintains consistency across the codebase
- Ensures accessibility for international developers
- Follows industry standard practices for open source projects
- Aligns with the tech stack documentation (React, TypeScript, Electron)

## Application
This language specification applies to:
- All TypeScript/JavaScript comments
- JSDoc documentation
- README files and markdown documentation
- Component prop descriptions
- Function and method comments
- Error messages and console logs
- Git commit messages
- Code variable naming (camelCase English)
